  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I get a job in Infosys off campus?",
  "response": "Getting a job at Infosys off-campus involves several steps. Here\u2019s a guide to help you navigate the process:\n\n### 1. **Understand the Requirements:**\n   - **Educational Background:** Typically, Infosys hires graduates from engineering and technical background, but they may also consider candidates from other fields like MBA, BCA, B.Sc., etc.\n   - **Percentage Criteria:** Most companies, including Infosys, may have a minimum percentage criterion (commonly around 60% throughout your academic career).\n\n### 2. **Build a Strong Resume:**\n   - **Highlight Relevant Skills:** Focus on including programming languages, tools, and technologies relevant to the positions you are applying for (e.g., Python, Java, SQL).\n   - **Projects and Internships:** Include any relevant projects or internships that showcase your skills and experience.\n\n### 3. **Prepare for the Recruitment Process:**\n   - **Aptitude Tests:** Infosys often conducts online aptitude tests that include quantitative, verbal, and reasoning sections. Practice sample papers and online assessment platforms.\n   - **Technical Interview:** Be prepared for a technical interview where you may be asked about algorithms, data structures, and core concepts related to your field.\n   - **HR Interview:** This interview typically focuses on behavioral questions and assessing your fit for the company culture.\n\n### 4. **Apply Through Official Sources:**\n   - **Infosys Careers Page:** Regularly check the official Infosys careers website for job openings. Make sure to apply through their portal.\n   - **Job Portals:** Websites like Naukri, LinkedIn, and Indeed also list job openings for Infosys. Keep your profiles updated on these platforms.\n\n### 5. **Network:**\n   - **Leverage Professional Networks:** Connect with current or former Infosys employees on platforms like LinkedIn. They may provide insights or refer you internally.\n   - **Participate in Campus Recruitment Drives:** Even if you're not currently in college, attending workshops or seminars at colleges that partner with Infosys can provide valuable contacts.\n\n### 6. **Certification and Skills Development:**\n   - **Online Courses:** Consider getting certifications in relevant technologies or domains (such as cloud computing, data science, etc.) to enhance your profile.\n   - **Projects and Contributions:** Work on projects (open source or personal) that you can showcase in your resume or during interviews.\n\n### 7. **Follow Up:**\n   - After applying, you may want to follow up occasionally to express your continued interest in the position, especially if you have connections within the company.\n\n### 8. **Stay Updated:**\n   - Keep an eye on Infosys for news about recruitment drives, campus selections, or any other events that may open up job opportunities.\n\n### Conclusion\nWhile landing a job at Infosys off-campus may be competitive, persistence, preparation, and the right approach can increase your chances. Good luck!",
